+{"id":"franken_numpy-sksm","title":"Add native fnp-python geomspace positive-real fast path","description":"mock-code-finder found that crates/fnp-python/src/lib.rs implements geomspace as an unconditional thin wrapper around numpy.geomspace, even for the simple positive finite scalar cases that the Rust core UFuncArray::geomspace_endpoint already supports. This leaves a fake/native-placeholder path in the Python surface: common np.geomspace(start, stop, num, endpoint, dtype) calls never exercise FrankenNumPy's native implementation. Implement a conservative native fast path for positive finite scalar start/stop with axis=0 and supported float dtype/None, preserving fallback to NumPy for negative endpoints, complex inputs, vectorized axis behavior, unsupported dtype, and other cases. Add tests that compare positive scalar default and endpoint=False dtype=float32 behavior against NumPy while existing fallback cases remain covered.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-28T19:40:33.370481882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-28T19:40:37.147762677Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["fnp-python","mock-code-finder","parity"]}
